    "For instance, in [3] the authors introduced some attention questions to exclude bots and users providing random answers just to obtain the reward.",
    "Overall, only the 44% of users answered correctly to those questions and could thus be considered reliable.",
    "Other works proposed metrics to automatically evaluate the quality of the explanations of HAR systems.",
    "Specifically, the work in [2] proposed an explanation score based on a knowledge-model (i.e., a set of logic rules).",
    "Such knowledge-model encodes the relationships between smart-home events and activities, and it is used to evaluate whether the explanation identified the concepts that explain (even partially) the predicted activities."
